column18: We scraped away what we interpreted to be dead bark to reveal live bark, identified by a color change (typically darker to lighter), increase in moisture content (wet), and fibrous texture. We placed the pistond dendrometer on the outermost live bark.

column12: Threaded rods not srewed in all the way (yet). Screwed all the way in 9-AUG-2015
column18: We threaded rods approximately 15 cm in total length into the tree after pre-drilling to approximately 8 cm. The idea is to sink the end of the threaded rod into the dead heartwood of the tree, to fix the piston dendrometer in a tree frame of reference.
